Visualizing direct routes in the US through a single file import from Federal Aviation Administration prezipped coupon data

By Gadi Dreyfuss
*Raw R file download available HERE

Project Info

This project impetus is as a component of a larger effort as part of my thesis exploring the economic impact of airlines to regional spoke cities in the United States. As such, I intended for this project to be the precursor to more in depth data analysis to come to explore data sources, process them analytically, and create the framework for the model and methodology I can continue develop throughout my thesis.

Project Objective

Visualize non-stop flight connections in any quarter from prezipped, FAA data.

My data sources came primarily from the Federal Aviation Administrations Data Profile: Airline Origin and Destination Survey (DB1B). Other data include .CSV files indicating the latitude and longitude of the referenced airports around the world.

See bottom of page for URLs.

Project

Set origin target (enter your own, by default it is SWF)

Then set working directory.

setwd("/Users/gdrey/Desktop/proj/wd")

The working directory was changed to /Users/gdrey/Desktop/proj/wd inside a notebook chunk. The working directory will be reset when the chunk is finished running. Use the knitr root.dir option in the setup chunk to change the working directory for notebook chunks.

Load libraries needed for project.

There is a conflict between tidyverse and dplyr packages. Implement this filter to address conflicts.

Convert .ZIP to .CSV

Because the quarter data is downloaded in a .zip file, it can be extracted to the folder. The only action required is to paste the pathname of the zip file and the desired location of the data.

Load data

The first dataset is a .CSV of airports, their IATA Codes, and coordinates. The second dataset refers to the DB1B coupon data from FAA.

The first dataset can be downloaded here: gdrey.github.io/files/gis_4201c/data/airports.csv

The second dataset (and DB1B coupon data) can be found by navigating to:

https://www.transtats.bts.gov/DATABASES.ASP?Mode_ID=1&Mode_Desc=Aviation&Subject_ID2=0%20&pn=1 > Airline Origin and Destination Survey (DB1B) > DB1B Coupon Download (bottom right) > [select target quarter and year] > Prezipped file > Download

airports <- read.csv("/Users/gdrey/Desktop/proj/data/airports.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE, header = TRUE)
coupon <- read_csv("/Users/gdrey/Desktop/proj/data/Origin_and_Destination_Survey_DB1BCoupon_2018_1.csv")

There are many columns, select only needed columns

select_col_airports<-select(airports, "iata_code","latitude_deg","longitude_deg")
select_col_coupon<-select(coupon,"Year","Origin","Dest")

Based on previous visualization, remove outlier coordinates (PHL)

select_col_airports<- select_col_airports[-c(38593), ]

Perform QC by checking to see if the selected columns made it in.

head(select_col_airports,5)

head(select_col_coupon,5)

Merge data

Merge the airport coordinate data and origin/destination data.

merge_to_origin <- merge(select_col_coupon, select_col_airports, by.x = "Origin", by.y = "iata_code",all.x=TRUE)
route_data <- merge(merge_to_origin, select_col_airports, by.x = "Dest", by.y = "iata_code",all.x=TRUE)

Perform QC to see if route data appears merged, for extra QC, copy/paste coordinates of origin airport into https://www.google.com/maps

Rename columns to make more sense.

Perform QC to ensure column names were changed

Airport_origin_0[!complete.cases(Airport_origin_0),]

Airport_origin <- na.omit(Airport_origin_0)

Create base visualization (map)

Basemap of contiguous US (can implement World to catch scope of Alaska and Hawaii on map)

Load the route data onto the basemap

allUSA <- ggplot() + usMap +
  geom_curve(data=Airport_origin,
             aes(x=origin_long, y=origin_lat, xend=dest_long, yend=dest_lat),
             col="#00008b",
             size=.2,
             curvature=0.2) +
  geom_point(data=Airport_origin,
             aes(x=origin_long, y=origin_lat), 
             colour="blue",
             size=1) +
  geom_point(data=Airport_origin,
             aes(x=dest_long, y=dest_lat), 
             colour="blue") +
  theme(axis.line=element_blank(),
        axis.text.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.y=element_blank(),
        axis.title.x=element_blank(),
        axis.title.y=element_blank(),
        axis.ticks=element_blank(),
        plot.title=element_text(hjust=0.5, size=12)) +
  ggtitle("United State Flight Route Map")
